    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-03T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-03T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 3, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 75. Repeated information Paris 169.
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> tells us that violent attacks
                    against Dien Bien Phu have suddenly stopped. French <pb facs="0703" n="677"
                        xml:id="pg_677"/> are not certain what this means since they believe Viet
                    Minh has capability of carrying the fortress by storm. They suspect that attacks
                    against Dien Bien Phu are being orchestrated with Geneva negotiations with
                    signals being called from Geneva.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
